# Well-formed structural fixture (step 1)

## Goal
A toy CLI that echoes its argv.

## Inputs and outputs
- argv: any positional args
- stdin: ignored
- stdout: argv joined by spaces, plus newline
- stderr: empty
- exit codes: 0 on success

## Error taxonomy
N/A: no error paths in v0

## File-system contract
N/A

## Concurrency
N/A

## Performance bounds
N/A

## Acceptance examples
1. argv=["echo","hi"] stdin="" -> stdout="hi\n" stderr="" exit=0
2. argv=["echo","a","b"] stdin="" -> stdout="a b\n" stderr="" exit=0
3. argv=["echo"] stdin="" -> stdout="\n" stderr="" exit=0

## Refusing examples
1. (none in v0)

## Out of scope
- everything except echo
